node.statement: n=4 SYMMETRIC SUBCASE (e3=0) PROVED. For symmetric quartics, 1/Phi_4 = 2E*phi(t) where phi(t)=t(1-4t)/(1+12t) is strictly concave. General n=4: 1/Phi_4=-disc/(4IJ) where I=e2^2+12e4>0, J=2e2^3-8e2e4+9e3^2<0. Cross term (1/6)e2p*e2q in g_4 blocks coefficient-additivity approach. 659-term excess has no quadratic form. See findings_n4_coefficient.md.
